# GitHub Phase Workflow

- Start each new phase on a new branch from `main`.
- Branch naming format: `phase<number> <brief line about the phase>`.
- Keep all work for that phase on that phase branch.
- Make incremental commits for each feature/task completed during the phase.
- Do not open a PR before phase completion unless explicitly asked.
- When the phase is agreed complete, open one PR from the phase branch for review.
- After merge, start the next phase from updated `main` on a fresh phase branch.

## Example

- `phase1 auth endpoints and token refresh`
- `phase2 email parsing and status updates`
